On your feet.
What's wrong with you, huh?

10
00:01:12,455 --> 00:01:15,409
- Who are you?
- I'm Navy SEALs.

11
00:01:16,834 --> 00:01:19,207
- You know how to use this?
- I'm a diplomat.

12
00:01:19,963 --> 00:01:22,039
Point and shoot. Let's go.

13
00:01:31,641 --> 00:01:33,680
Let's go, let's go.

14
00:01:36,938 --> 00:01:37,969
My leg.

15
00:01:54,831 --> 00:01:57,666
<i>Following in his father's footsteps</i>
<i>as a Naval aviator,

16
00:01:57,834 --> 00:01:59,743
<i>Lieutenant Commander</i>
<i>Harmon Rabb Jr.

17
00:01:59,919 --> 00:02:02,410
<i>Suffered a crash while landing</i>
<i>his Tomcat

18
00:02:02,672 --> 00:02:05,044
<i>on a storm-tossed carrier at sea.

19
00:02:05,216 --> 00:02:06,794
<i>Diagnosed with night blindness,

20
00:02:06,968 --> 00:02:09,969
<i>Harm transferred to the Navy's</i>
<i>Judge Advocate General Corps,

21
00:02:10,138 --> 00:02:14,432
<i>which investigates, defends</i>
<i>and prosecutes the law of the sea.

22
00:02:14,601 --> 00:02:17,436
<i>There, with fellow JAG lawyer</i>
<i>Major Sarah MacKenzie,

23
00:02:17,603 --> 00:02:19,726
<i>he now fights in and out</i>
<i>of the courtroom

24
00:02:19,897 --> 00:02:25,354
<i>with the same daring and tenacity</i>
<i>that made him a top gun in the air.

25
00:03:14,037 --> 00:03:15,697
Undersecretary of State
Lawrence Culbertson

26
00:03:15,873 --> 00:03:18,198
was rescued last night
from Hamas terrorists.

27
00:03:18,375 --> 00:03:20,831
A Lt. Curtis Rivers, platoon
commander from SEAL Team 7,

28
00:03:22,379 --> 00:03:24,455
got Culbertson out single-handedly.

29
00:03:24,631 --> 00:03:26,173
- Attention on deck.
- As you were.

30
00:03:26,341 --> 00:03:27,456
Leave it to the SEALs.

31
00:03:27,634 --> 00:03:28,832
A worthy sentiment, commander,

32
00:03:29,011 --> 00:03:31,336
since they are the most effective
strike force in the world.

33
00:03:31,513 --> 00:03:32,758
Absolutely, admiral.

34
00:03:32,973 --> 00:03:35,546
Apparently, the president
agrees with me.

35
00:03:35,726 --> 00:03:37,303
He asked the Secretary of Navy

36
00:03:37,477 --> 00:03:41,142
to nominate Lt. Rivers
for the Medal of Honour.

37
00:03:41,314 --> 00:03:44,150
That must have been
one hell of a rescue, sir.

38
00:03:45,318 --> 00:03:49,150
Culbertson's the president's point man
in the Middle East peace talks.

39
00:03:49,322 --> 00:03:52,109
Rivers saved him without regard
for his own personal safety

40
00:03:52,284 --> 00:03:55,285
and accounted
for eight enemy casualties.

41
00:03:56,830 --> 00:04:00,199
Anyway, SECNAV
wants JAG to determine

44
00:04:05,297 --> 00:04:07,455
Not just the incident, major.

45
00:04:07,632 --> 00:04:09,839
The president wants assurance
there is nothing

46
00:04:10,010 --> 00:04:12,679
in Lt. Rivers' past
that might cause embarrassment.

47
00:04:12,887 --> 00:04:14,382
To Lt. Rivers or the president?

48
00:04:15,056 --> 00:04:17,263
Lt. Rivers and his men
have returned

49
00:04:17,434 --> 00:04:19,841
to the Naval Special Warfare Centre,
Coronado.

50
00:04:20,019 --> 00:04:22,427
You will find him on instructor detail.

51
00:04:22,605 --> 00:04:24,147
All of us to California?

52
00:04:25,233 --> 00:04:27,391
Unless you have other plans.

53
00:04:27,569 --> 00:04:29,478
No, sir.

54
00:04:29,946 --> 00:04:34,240
Good. I expect
a full and fair evaluation.

55
00:04:34,409 --> 00:04:37,196
Ignore the politics.

56
00:04:37,370 --> 00:04:41,913
And remember, you need testimony
from two eyewitnesses.

57
00:04:42,083 --> 00:04:43,874
Dismissed.

58
00:04:44,043 --> 00:04:45,668
Aye, aye, sir.

59
00:04:48,214 --> 00:04:50,372
And don't let the fact that
I'm a former SEAL

60
00:04:50,550 --> 00:04:52,673
influence your decision.

61
00:04:52,844 --> 00:04:54,920
- No, sir.
- Absolutely not, sir.

62
00:04:59,016 --> 00:05:00,676
JAG headquarters, this is...

63
00:05:00,852 --> 00:05:05,348
We just got our orders, Harriet.
We leave in a few hours.

64
00:05:05,523 --> 00:05:08,393
I know it wrecks our plans.

65
00:05:08,860 --> 00:05:13,189
I'm gonna miss you too.
I can't wait to get back.

66
00:05:14,740 --> 00:05:16,199
Really?

67
00:05:16,951 --> 00:05:19,157
No. It's just that I've heard
that stiletto heels

68
00:05:19,328 --> 00:05:21,819
can be bad for your ankles.

69
00:05:23,124 --> 00:05:26,374
I'll get right on that,
Captain Harwich.

70
00:05:26,836 --> 00:05:29,208
I didn't know Bruce Harwich
wore stiletto heels.

71
00:05:29,380 --> 00:05:31,337
Sir, did you know that
the first Navy SEAL who won

72
00:05:31,507 --> 00:05:33,749
the Congressional Medal of Honour
was Senator Bob Kerrey?

73
00:05:33,926 --> 00:05:35,669
Did you know
that you're beet red right now?

74
00:05:35,845 --> 00:05:38,086
You know, he wasn't a senator
when he received the medal.

75
00:05:38,264 --> 00:05:39,592
He was a lieutenant, JG, sir.

76
00:05:39,765 --> 00:05:41,010
Nice diversion, Bud.

77
00:05:41,183 --> 00:05:45,015
Yeah, he lost a leg leading a SEAL raid
against Viet Cong snipers,

78
00:05:45,187 --> 00:05:49,315
but was still able to direct
a counterattack which... Yes, sir?

79
00:05:49,483 --> 00:05:52,021
Get on the computer and pull up
everything you can on Lt. Rivers.

80
00:05:52,194 --> 00:05:55,230
- Let's see who we're dealing with.
- Aye, aye, sir.

81
00:06:07,334 --> 00:06:10,039
I spoke with the Secretary of the Navy
personally about Lt. Rivers.

82
00:06:10,212 --> 00:06:13,129
So why is the Judge Advocate
General Corps involved in this?

83
00:06:13,298 --> 00:06:16,216
This is strictly routine, sir.

84
00:06:16,802 --> 00:06:21,215
My guess is that the SECNAV
is routinely covering his butt.

85
00:06:21,390 --> 00:06:24,391
Well, we have no knowledge
of that, sir.

86
00:06:25,352 --> 00:06:27,428
Do you folks believe in heroes?

87
00:06:28,021 --> 00:06:29,053
Yes, sir.

88
00:06:30,315 --> 00:06:31,774
I suppose so.

89
00:06:31,942 --> 00:06:33,816
I never did.

90
00:06:33,986 --> 00:06:38,529
When soldiers shoot at each other, l...
It usually means that I've failed.

91
00:06:39,533 --> 00:06:42,403
But this man, this Lt. Rivers,

92
00:06:43,662 --> 00:06:45,536
he risked his life to protect me.

93
00:06:46,123 --> 00:06:47,665
He never hesitated,
he never doubted.

94
00:06:47,833 --> 00:06:51,700
He just stood there in the line of fire,
shooting back,

95
00:06:51,878 --> 00:06:54,665
and then he carried me to safety.

96
00:06:54,840 --> 00:06:56,916
He didn't even know me.

97
00:06:59,427 --> 00:07:01,716
That's a true hero.

98
00:07:06,393 --> 00:07:07,768
<i>Navy beans and GI gravy

99
00:07:07,936 --> 00:07:10,509
<i>Navy beans and GI gravy

100
00:07:10,689 --> 00:07:13,358
<i>Gee, I'm glad I joined the Navy

101
